item.title: Annual AACC Yard Sale
item.description:
Parking Lot F
Saturday, June 4, 2016, 8am – 12pm

Whether you have treasures to sell or are looking for a unique item to add to your household, plan to attend Anne Arundel Community College's 12th Annual Community Yard Sale on Saturday, June 4, from 8 a.m. to noon, in Parking Lot F on the Arnold campus. Tables are $25 if reserved on or before May 31 and $30 afterward. To reserve a table, call 410-777-2724 or 410-777-2614 or click here for registration form

You also can mail your information and check to Events Services, Student Union Room 140, Anne Arundel Community College, 101 College Parkway, Arnold, Md. 21401. Be sure to include your name, address, email address, phone number, the number of spaces you wish to reserve and the amount enclosed.

The day's events include a car show and a swap and meet. In addition, AACC's Lifelong Learning once again will have a Yard Sale Rescue contest. Purchase something you plan to refashion, take it to the Lifelong Learning booth for a "before" photo and once you've completed the transformation, email the "after" photo to Lifelong Learning. Prizes will be awarded in five categories. For information, call 410-777-2121.

To reach Parking Lot F, turn onto West Campus Drive from Route 2, Gov. Ritchie Highway, at the YMCA at Arnold and follow the signs. Chick-fil-A is offering food for sale, and no other booths can sell food. A Goodwill truck will arrive at noon to collect all unsold and unwanted items.

item.description:
Friday, June 10, 5:30pm – Saturday, June 11, 2016, 1:30pm

AACC is committed to providing current and progressive technology to enhance and support the college mission.

In order to provide superior service to the college community, regular maintenance is required. In an effort to lessen the impact on students during our routine downtime scheduled on Friday evenings, AACC has implemented a new downtime schedule effective January 2014.


System Downtime Schedule
Scheduled maintenance occurs on the  2nd Friday of each month starting at 5:30 p.m. for updates to all products and systems that support MyAACC to ensure that all system outages affecting students are performed at the same time. Student related services such as Canvas LMS, MyAACC portal,
www.aacc.edu, student email access and the Self Services tab will only be affected once a month. We will continue to reschedule any downtime that coincides with a major college event, such as final exams.

item.description:
Friday, July 8, 6:30pm – Saturday, July 9, 2016, 1:30am

AACC is committed to providing current and progressive technology to enhance and support the college mission.

In order to provide superior service to the college community, regular maintenance is required. In an effort to lessen the impact on students during our routine downtime scheduled on Friday evenings, AACC has implemented a new downtime schedule effective January 2014.


System Downtime Schedule
Scheduled maintenance occurs on the 2nd Friday of each month starting at 6:30 p.m. for updates to all products and systems that support MyAACC to ensure that all system outages affecting students are performed at the same time. Student related services such as Canvas LMS, MyAACC portal,

www.aacc.edu, student email access and the Self Services tab will only be affected once a month. We will continue to reschedule any downtime that coincides with a major college event, such as final exams.

item.title: Regularly Scheduled System Downtime
item.description:
Friday, August 12, 6:30pm – Saturday, August 13, 2016, 1:30am

AACC is committed to providing current and progressive technology to enhance and support the college mission.

In order to provide superior service to the college community, regular maintenance is required. In an effort to lessen the impact on students during our routine downtime scheduled on Friday evenings, AACC has implemented a new downtime schedule effective January 2014.


System Downtime Schedule
Scheduled maintenance occurs on the 2nd Friday of each month starting at 6:30 p.m. for updates to all products and systems that support MyAACC to ensure that all system outages affecting students are performed at the same time. Student related services such as Canvas LMS, MyAACC portal,

www.aacc.edu, student email access and the Self Services tab will only be affected once a month. We will continue to reschedule any downtime that coincides with a major college event, such as final exams.

item.description:
CRSC*245 - Classroom "Accounting"
Tuesday, September 6, 2016, 2 – 6pm

In the AACC Anime Club, students who are fans of Japanese animation and entertainment gather to discuss and view examples of such. Activities consist of viewing anime voted upon by the members of the club, with the last hour set aside for members to bring in their own favorite series to share with others in the club. Other meetings consist of movie days, themed days- typically around a specific genre of anime- and presentations by club members that give insight on Japan's culture, history, and popular culture. The club visits one anime convention per semester, and also hosts an end-of-the-semester party for club members during finals week. Fall semester contains an additional Halloween party, held in October, and Spring semester has a Spring Break party held before Spring Break.

item.description:
Friday, September 9, 6:30pm – Saturday, September 10, 2016, 1:30am

AACC is committed to providing current and progressive technology to enhance and support the college mission.

In order to provide superior service to the college community, regular maintenance is required. In an effort to lessen the impact on students during our routine downtime scheduled on Friday evenings, AACC has implemented a new downtime schedule effective January 2014.


System Downtime Schedule
Scheduled maintenance occurs on the 2nd Friday of each month starting at 6:30 p.m. for updates to all products and systems that support MyAACC to ensure that all system outages affecting students are performed at the same time. Student related services such as Canvas LMS, MyAACC portal,

www.aacc.edu, student email access and the Self Services tab will only be affected once a month. We will continue to reschedule any downtime that coincides with a major college event, such as final exams.

AACC is committed to providing current and progressive technology to enhance and support the college mission.

System Downtime Schedule
Scheduled maintenance occurs on the 2nd Friday of each month starting at 6:30 p.m. for updates to all products and systems that support MyAACC to ensure that all system outages affecting students are performed at the same time. Student related services such as Canvas LMS, MyAACC portal,

www.aacc.edu, student email access and the Self Services tab will only be affected once a month. We will continue to reschedule any downtime that coincides with a major college event, such as final exams.

item.description:
The Professor Robert E. Kauffman Theater
Friday, November 18, 2016, 6 – 10pm

A timeless program suitable for all ages and not to be missed as critically acclaimed pianist Pavel Gintov returns to AACC.

$ 9 senior citizens, groups, active military, outside students, AACC employees & children under 10
